      "term": "Fuller/Riser",
      "meaning": "The spine of the sword. A <i>fuller</i> is a shallow groove that runs down each flat, along the sword's spine. The fuller lightens the sword, but in such a way that it retains stiffness for cutting. Note that some swords, particularly those designed to emphasize the thrust, do not have a fuller, but rather have a wide, diamond cross-sectioned blade. The thicker \"spine\" makes the sword stiffer, and is called a <i>riser</i>."
